translated: Kempe, Sven Ragnar, provincial physician, Tranås, b. 2/7/1895 in Bjurholm, Västerbotten County, son of provincial physician Sven K. and Anna Olsson. Married on 31st to Gudrun Ericson. Children: Bertil b. 1931, Lars b. 1933, Birgitta b. 1936. Education: graduated from Skara in 1915, medical candidate in Stockholm in 1919, and medical doctorate there in 1925. Assistant doctor at Östersund Hospital in 1922, assistant doctor and temporarily acting house physician at Högbo Sanatorium in 1924, temporarily acting doctor for railways and mines in Malmberget for six months in 1925 and 1926, temporarily acting provincial physician in Gällivare district for six months during the same time period, shorter periods in Älvsbyn and Håby districts in 1926, second assistant doctor at Garnison Hospital in Stockholm surgical department from 1926 to 1928, temporarily acting house physician at Västerås Hospital surgical department in 1928, at Eksjö and ApeJviken Sanatorium in 1929, second assistant doctor at Karlstad Hospital surgical department from 1929 to 1930, provincial physician and district medical officer in Långav district from 1930 to 1936, provincial physician in Tranås district since 1937.
